article.headline: Oral Roberts 77, Valparaiso 58
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. (AP) -- Calum MacLeod scored 18 points Saturday night and Valparaiso held off a second-half comeback to beat Calumet 84-65. The Crusaders (1-0) led 40-27 at halftime and used a 15-6 run at the start of the second period to help build their lead to 64-38. Tom Radtke, who had only five points in the first half, then started the rally for the Division II Crimson Wave (1-1). Radtke hit 8-of-11 shots in the final period and finished with 26 points for the game, including all 18 of his team's points during one stretch midway through the final half. The Wave cut the Valpo lead to 79-65 with two minutes to go but couldn't come any closer. Arden Skoglund hit two free throws for the Crusaders and Matt Bennett added a basket down the stretch. Evinn Herring added 20 points for Calumet, while no one else had more than 5 points. Four other players backed MacLeod with double-figures scoring for Valparaiso. Urule Igbavboa added 15 points and 15 rebounds, Jarryd Lloyd finished with 13 points, Shawn Huff had 12 and Brandon McPherson scored 10 for the Crusaders, who held off Radtke's flurry of points by shooting 59 percent in the second half.
